I am going to write my bad experience in Spanish as well below. También, voy a escribir en español mi mal experiencia aqui abajo.  I went to this place as a recommendation from my friend because she wanted to check it out. They offered outdoor seating now due to corona. Overall when we first arrived we just wanted drinks but after awhile of enjoying the music and atmosphere, we decided to order food, at this point we are there for a good while. I ordered the food in spanish with the woman with glasses at the bar instead of the waitress. Big mistake. I told her what me and my friend wanted. That is when the misunderstanding started, I asked for shrimp tacos and carne asada tacos for me. But the woman at the bar noted it as a platter which I was not aware of. Then back with the waitress, my friend decides she wants rice and refried beans also with her tacos, so she orders it. Food arrives, I don't see my carne asada tacos, I mentioned it and instead of realizing the error, the woman with glasses from the bar says I do not get my refund for the food because the platter comes with rice and refried beans and my friend was eating it. I told her my friend ordered herself rice and refried beans, we only received one order of it. The waitress confirms she took an order from my friend. The woman with the glasses begins looking around for a second tray of rice and refried beans, like we hid it. 🤦🏾‍♀️🤦🏾‍♀️🤦🏾‍♀️ My friend paid for her food and they charged for her order of rice and refried beans. So there should have been two, this is not my fault. She was incredibly rude to me, even after I explain to her, she did not care what I had to say. There was sno manager to speak to either to clear it up. It ruined our mood and night. The waitress, she was done for the night but stayed and was just so sweet with us, she even offered to pay for my tacos when she did not have to. You should expect that from the person that took my order wrong. I will not be returning there and neither is my friend, if that is how they treat customers, be prepared to blamed and treated with carelessness. No wonder they have a low reviews with people like that woman running the bar. Be wary of her. ---- Fui a este lugar por recomendación de mi amiga porque quería verlo. Ofrecían asientos al aire libre ahora debido a la corona. En general, cuando llegamos, solo queríamos bebidas, pero después de un tiempo de disfrutar de la música y el ambiente, decidimos pedir comida, en este punto estamos allí por un buen rato. Le dije que mi amiga se había pedido arroz y frijoles refritos, solo recibimos una orden. La camarera confirma que tomó una orden de mi amiga. I am giving Los 3 Potrillos a 1 Star rating because of their blatant racism. I never liked to call a place races or utilized the race card but when it is needed I will use it. Before I can say it was racism let me tell you what happened and you can decide for yourself I stepped into the restaurant to get some food at 11:30 a.m. when I walked inside there was a Spanish customer sitting at the bar and was waiting for his food. I sat right next to him The workers didn't even acknowledge me I took a menu looked at it and waited to order,15 minutes went past and still not one of the four workers acknowledge me being there at 11:50 a family of four came inside the restaurant they were seated was given water a menu and then the waitress went to them and proceeded to take their order, meanwhile I am still sitting at the bar waiting for someone to take my order.  As a 50 year old African American man I found that to be a slap in my face especially since the family of four was of Latin descent and they clearly came to the restaurant after me. Clearly the workers need to understand that you don't treat customers like that. I was appalled and disgusted with their actions there is never and I mean never any reason to treat anyone like this I'm sure with my whole heart if I was Spanish or Latin descent I would have been served and I think the worst part that this is I'm married to a Spanish woman so I know how to speak the language very well and I know when I'm being ignored. I hope that Los Tres Potrillos look at this review and understand that they lost a very good customer and a lot of business because I will make sure that I spread this word about how I was treated.

MÉXICO 🇲🇽 Eat the World NYC review: Sunset Park is not really the type of place that people go out drinking at bars, as most of its residents are families and from places where drinking culture requires meals to be involved as well. One place that is an exception to this rule and has a real bar is Los Tres Potrillos on the north side of the neighborhood. With a couple TVs usually showing football, I have been using it every once in a while to have a few beers during a Liga MX match or just when mood required getting out of the house.  Besides the bar and nice staff, one of the things that keeps me returning is their amazing plate of house nachos. Sometimes you just need nachos, and the nachos los tres potrillos is possibly as good as it gets. There are a few meat options, but the al pastor is the best with these and also adds pineapple to the rest of the numerous ingredients.
